      "content": "i know you're supposed to say that because you're an ai, but it doesn't change the reality. i look at them and all i see is the debt i'm putting on them, the stress i cause just by existing. it feels so selfish to keep hanging on when i know they'd have a much cleaner, easier life if they didn't have to worry about me. it almost feels like the most responsible thing to do is just step out of the way for them.",
